{
    "chapter": 70,
    "verses": {
        "1": {
            "verses": {
                "70:1": {
                    "id": 1
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>A petitioner petitioned, a supplicator supplicated [for], an impending chastisement</p>"
        },
        "2": {
            "verses": {
                "70:2": {
                    "id": 2
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>— which in the case of the disbelievers none can avert: this was al-Nadr b. al-Hrith who said, `O God, if this be indeed the truth from You ... [then rain down upon us stones from the heaven' [Q. 8:32],</p>"
        },
        "3": {
            "verses": {
                "70:3": {
                    "id": 3
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>from God (mina'Llhi is semantically connected to wqi`in, `impending'), Lord of the Ascensions, the ascension routes of the angels, which are the heavens.</p>"
        },
        "4": {
            "verses": {
                "70:4": {
                    "id": 4
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>To Him, to the place in the heaven to which His command descends, ascend (read [feminine person] ta`ruju or [masculine person] ya`ruju) the angels and the Spirit, Gabriel, in a day (f yawmin is semantically connected to an omitted clause, that is to say, `[in a day] in which the chastisement befalls them', on the Day of Resurrection) whose span is fifty thousand years, from the perspective of the disbeliever, on account of the calamities he will encounter in it — but as for the believer, it [the mentioned day] will be easier for him than an obligatory prayer which he performs in this world, as stated in hadth.</p>"
        },
        "5": {
            "verses": {
                "70:5": {
                    "id": 5
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>So be patient — this was [revealed] before he [the Prophet] was commanded to fight — with a graceful patience, that is, one in which there is no anguish.</p>"
        },
        "6": {
            "verses": {
                "70:6": {
                    "id": 6
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>Lo! they see it, that is, the chastisement, as [being] far off, as never taking place;</p>"
        },
        "7": {
            "verses": {
                "70:7": {
                    "id": 7
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<h2>while We see it [to be] near, taking place without a doubt.</h2>"
        },
        "8": {
            "verses": {
                "70:8": {
                    "id": 8
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>The day when the heaven will be (yawma taknu'l-sam'u is semantically connected to an omitted clause, implicitly taken to be yaqa`u, `it will take place') as molten silver,</p>"
        },
        "9": {
            "verses": {
                "70:9": {
                    "id": 9
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>and the mountains will be as flakes of wool, in terms of [their] lightness and [their] floating about in the wind.</p>"
        },
        "10": {
            "verses": {
                "70:10": {
                    "id": 10
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>And no friend will inquire about his friend, [no] relative [will inquire] about his relative, each being preoccupied with his own predicament.</p>"
        },
        "11": {
            "verses": {
                "70:11": {
                    "id": 11
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>They will [however] be made to see them, that is, friends will catch sight of one another, recognising one another but refraining from speaking [to one another] (the sentence [yubassarnahum] is a new [independent] one). The guilty one will desire, the disbeliever will yearn, to ransom himself from the chastisement of that day (read [min `adhbi] yawmi'dhin or [min `adhbin] yawma'idhin) at the price of his children,</p>"
        },
        "12": {
            "verses": {
                "70:12": {
                    "id": 12
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<h2>and his companion, his wife, and his brother,</h2>"
        },
        "13": {
            "verses": {
                "70:13": {
                    "id": 13
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>and his kin, his clan ([expressed as fasla] because he is a [detached] part [fasl] of it) that had sheltered him, embraced him,</p>"
        },
        "14": {
            "verses": {
                "70:14": {
                    "id": 14
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>and all who are on earth, if it, that ransom, might then deliver him (thumma yunjhi is a supplement to yaftad, `to ransom himself').</p>"
        },
        "15": {
            "verses": {
                "70:15": {
                    "id": 15
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>Nay! — a refutation of his wish. Lo! [for him] it, namely, the Fire, will be the Churning Fire (laz) — a name for Hell, [so called] because it churns its flames [tatalazz] against the disbelievers,</p>"
        },
        "16": {
            "verses": {
                "70:16": {
                    "id": 16
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>ripping out the scalp (shaw is the plural of shawt, the skin of the head);</p>"
        },
        "17": {
            "verses": {
                "70:17": {
                    "id": 17
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>it will call him who turned his back and ignored, faith, saying [to him]: `To me ! to me [come hither]!',</p>"
        },
        "18": {
            "verses": {
                "70:18": {
                    "id": 18
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>and amassed, wealth, then hoarded, keeping it in containers and refraining from paying from it what is God's due.</p>"
        },
        "19": {
            "verses": {
                "70:19": {
                    "id": 19
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<h2>Indeed man was created restless: (hal`an is an implied circumstantial qualifier, the explanation of which [follows]):</h2>"
        },
        "20": {
            "verses": {
                "70:20": {
                    "id": 20
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>when evil befalls him, [he is] anxious, at the point of that evil befalling [him],</p>"
        },
        "21": {
            "verses": {
                "70:21": {
                    "id": 21
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>and when good befalls him, [he is] grudging, at the point of that good befalling [him], that is to say, [when] wealth [befalls him], [he is grudging to give] of it what is due to God;</p>"
        },
        "22": {
            "verses": {
                "70:22": {
                    "id": 22
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<h2>except those who perform prayers, that is, the believers,</h2>"
        },
        "23": {
            "verses": {
                "70:23": {
                    "id": 23
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>those who maintain, [those who] regularly observe, their prayers,</p>"
        },
        "24": {
            "verses": {
                "70:24": {
                    "id": 24
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>and in whose wealth there is an acknowledged due, namely, alms,</p>"
        },
        "25": {
            "verses": {
                "70:25": {
                    "id": 25
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>for the beggar and the deprived, the [latter being the] one who refrains from begging and thus becomes deprived,</p>"
        },
        "26": {
            "verses": {
                "70:26": {
                    "id": 26
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>and who affirm the truth of the Day of Judgement, [of] Requital,</p>"
        },
        "27": {
            "verses": {
                "70:27": {
                    "id": 27
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>and who are apprehensive of the chastisement of their Lord —</p>"
        },
        "28": {
            "verses": {
                "70:28": {
                    "id": 28
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>lo! there is no security from the chastisement of their Lord, [from] its being sent down —</p>"
        },
        "29": {
            "verses": {
                "70:29": {
                    "id": 29
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<h2>and those who guard their private parts,</h2>"
        },
        "30": {
            "verses": {
                "70:30": {
                    "id": 30
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>except from their wives and those whom their right hands own, in the way of slavegirls, for in that case they are not blameworthy;</p>"
        },
        "31": {
            "verses": {
                "70:31": {
                    "id": 31
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>but whoever seeks beyond that, those are the infringers, who transgress [the bounds of] what is lawful [stepping] into what is unlawful;</p>"
        },
        "32": {
            "verses": {
                "70:32": {
                    "id": 32
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>and those who are keepers, [faithful] guardians, of their trusts (amntihim: a variant reading has the singular [amnatihim]), that to which they are entrusted of religion and the affairs of this world, and their covenant, the one taken from them regarding such things,</p>"
        },
        "33": {
            "verses": {
                "70:33": {
                    "id": 33
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>and who are forthwith with their testimony (bi-shahdatihim: a variant reading has the plural [bi- shahdtihim, `their testimonies']), [those who] offer them and do not withhold them,</p>"
        },
        "34": {
            "verses": {
                "70:34": {
                    "id": 34
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>and who preserve their prayers, by observing them in their appointed times.</p>"
        },
        "35": {
            "verses": {
                "70:35": {
                    "id": 35
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<h2>Those will be in Gardens, honoured.</h2>"
        },
        "36": {
            "verses": {
                "70:36": {
                    "id": 36
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>So what is wrong with those who disbelieve that they keep staring towards you (muhti`na is a circumstantial qualifier),</p>"
        },
        "37": {
            "verses": {
                "70:37": {
                    "id": 37
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<h2>to the right and to the left, of you, in droves? (`izna is also a circumstantial qualifier), in other words, in groups standing in circles, one next to the other, saying, in mockery of the believers, `Verily if [the likes of] these are to enter Paradise, we shall enter it before them'. God, exalted be He, says:</h2>"
        },
        "38": {
            "verses": {
                "70:38": {
                    "id": 38
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>Does each one of them hope to be admitted into a Garden of Bliss?</p>"
        },
        "39": {
            "verses": {
                "70:39": {
                    "id": 39
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>Nay! — meant to thwart their hopes of [entering] Paradise. Indeed We created them, as others, from what they know, from drops of sperm, and so one cannot hope for Paradise [merely] on account of this: one hopes for it by being God-fearing.</p>"
        },
        "40": {
            "verses": {
                "70:40": {
                    "id": 40
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>For verily (fa-l: l is extra) I swear by the Lord of the rising-places and the setting-places, of the sun, the moon and all the stars, that We are able</p>"
        },
        "41": {
            "verses": {
                "70:41": {
                    "id": 41
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>to replace [them], to bring in their place, with [others] better than them, and We are not to be outmanoeuvred, [We will not be] frustrated in this.</p>"
        },
        "42": {
            "verses": {
                "70:42": {
                    "id": 42
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>So leave them to indulge, in their falsehoods, and to play, in this world of theirs, until they encounter that day of theirs, in, which they are promised, chastisement;</p>"
        },
        "43": {
            "verses": {
                "70:43": {
                    "id": 43
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
